{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "FuchsSutugin",
        "description": "Fuchs-Sutugin transition-regime correction factor for aerosol mass transfer. f_FS = J/J_c is the ratio of the actual flux to the continuum-regime flux J_c; it interpolates between f_FS → 1 in the continuum limit (Kn ≪ 1) and f_FS → 0 in the free-molecular limit (Kn ≫ 1). The formula f_FS = 0.75α(1+Kn)/(Kn²+Kn+0.283Kn·α+0.75α) (Seinfeld & Pandis 2006, Chapter 12, Eq. 12.43) is the most widely used semi-empirical interpolation across the full Knudsen number range, and extends the original Fuchs (1934) result with an explicit accommodation-coefficient correction due to Sutugin. Migrated from Aerosol.jl src/mass_transfer.jl `FuchsSutugin`.",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "mass-transfer",
            "transition-regime",
            "knudsen-number",
            "seinfeld-pandis"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-21T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "Aerosol.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-wrq)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H. and Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd Edition. John Wiley & Sons. Chapter 12, Eq. 12.43 (Fuchs-Sutugin correction factor with accommodation coefficient)."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "FuchsSutugin": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H. and Pandis, S. N. (2006) Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics, 2nd Edition, Chapter 12, Eq. 12.43 — Fuchs-Sutugin semi-empirical interpolation for transition-regime mass transfer. Migrated from Aerosol.jl src/mass_transfer.jl `FuchsSutugin` (esm-wrq).",
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@FWrvp:src/mass_transfer.jl:117\n\nUpstream `FuchsSutugin` is an MTK `@component` with 2 parameters (Kn, α) and 1 variable f_FS(t) determined by one explicit algebraic equation with no time derivative — purely observed.\n\nEquation (S&P 2006, Eq. 12.43):\n  f_FS = 0.75α(1 + Kn) / (Kn² + Kn + 0.283Kn·α + 0.75α)   [dimensionless]\n\nPhysics: The formula interpolates between the continuum limit and the free-molecular limit:\n  Kn → 0 (continuum):      f_FS → 0.75α / (0.75α) = 1.0   (no correction)\n  Kn → ∞ (free-molecular): f_FS → 0.75α·Kn / Kn² = 0.75α/Kn → 0\n\nThe constant 0.283 is an empirical fitting coefficient from Fuchs and Sutugin (1971) that achieves continuity with the free-molecular regime kinetic theory result. The accommodation coefficient α (range 0 to 1] modulates both numerator and denominator; when α = 1, the formula reduces to the original Fuchs-Sutugin form without explicit accommodation.\n\nKnudsen number Kn = λ/R_p where λ is the gas mean free path and R_p the particle radius. In the atmosphere at standard conditions, λ ≈ 65 nm, so Kn ≈ 0.65 for R_p = 0.1 µm (sub-micron aerosol) and Kn ≈ 0.0065 for R_p = 10 µm (large droplet). The transition regime (Kn ~ 0.1–10) is where f_FS deviates significantly from both limits.\n\nf_FS is multiplied by the continuum-regime flux J_c (from MaxwellianFlux) to give the actual transition-regime flux J = f_FS × J_c. See MassTransfer for the complete coupled system.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-12): purely algebraic expression; a ratio of two polynomials in float64. The only nonlinearity is Kn²; round-off is ~1e-15 relative, and rel=1e-12 leaves three orders of headroom, consistent with the maxwellian_flux.esm convention."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-12
            },
            "variables": {
                "Kn": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Knudsen number Kn = λ/R_p, the ratio of the gas mean free path λ to the particle radius R_p. Kn ≪ 1 is the continuum regime; Kn ≫ 1 is the free-molecular regime; Kn ~ 1 is the transition regime where this correction is most important. Default 1.0 places the system in the middle of the transition regime."
                },
                "α": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Mass accommodation coefficient: dimensionless probability (0, 1] that a gas molecule striking the particle surface is irreversibly taken up. α = 1.0 (perfect accommodation) gives the original Fuchs (1934) formula; smaller α reduces f_FS and the effective mass-transfer rate. Default 1.0."
                },
                "f_FS": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Fuchs-Sutugin correction factor f_FS = J/J_c (Eq. 12.43): ratio of the actual molar flux to the continuum-regime flux. Dimensionless; range (0, 1]. Approaches 1 in the continuum limit (Kn ≪ 1), approaches 0 in the free-molecular limit (Kn ≫ 1). Multiply by J_c from MaxwellianFlux to obtain the transition-regime flux J.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [0.75, "α", {"op": "+", "args": [1.0, "Kn"]}]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "^", "args": ["Kn", 2]},
                                    "Kn",
                                    {"op": "*", "args": [0.283, "Kn", "α"]},
                                    {"op": "*", "args": [0.75, "α"]}
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            },
            "equations": [],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_conditions",
                    "description": "Default parameters: Kn=1.0, α=1.0. f_FS = 0.75×1×2 / (1+1+0.283+0.75) = 1.5/3.033 ≈ 0.4946. Anchors the model at its declared defaults in the middle of the transition regime.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "f_FS", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.49455984174085066, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-12}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "continuum_limit",
                    "description": "Near-continuum regime: Kn=0.01, α=1.0. f_FS → 1 as Kn → 0; numerically ≈ 0.9929. Verifies that the correction factor is close to unity when the particle is much larger than the mean free path.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"Kn": 0.01},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "f_FS", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.9928827022138336, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-12}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "free_molecular_limit",
                    "description": "Deep free-molecular regime: Kn=100.0, α=1.0. f_FS ≈ 0.75α/Kn → 0; numerically ≈ 0.00748. Verifies the strong suppression of the continuum-regime flux in the free-molecular regime.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"Kn": 100.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "f_FS", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.007478490085447303, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-12}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "reduced_accommodation",
                    "description": "Reduced accommodation coefficient: Kn=1.0, α=0.5. f_FS = 0.75×0.5×2 / (1+1+0.1415+0.375) = 0.75/2.5165 ≈ 0.2980. Verifies that lower α reduces f_FS — less accommodation means less efficient mass transfer even after the Knudsen-regime correction.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"α": 0.5},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "f_FS", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.2980329823167097, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-12}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "transition_regime",
                    "description": "Upper transition / lower free-molecular regime: Kn=10.0, α=1.0. f_FS ≈ 0.0726. Exercises the Kn² term in the denominator, which dominates at intermediate-to-large Kn.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"Kn": 10.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "f_FS", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.07263602746962494, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-12}}
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "fFS_vs_Kn",
                    "description": "Sweep Knudsen number Kn from 0.001 to 1000 log-spaced at α=1.0 (perfect accommodation). f_FS transitions from ≈1 in the continuum limit (Kn ≪ 1) to ≈0 in the free-molecular limit (Kn ≫ 1). The transition region Kn ~ 0.1–10 corresponds to sub-micron aerosol particles in the lower atmosphere (λ ≈ 65 nm, R_p ≈ 7 nm–650 nm).",
                    "initial_state": {"type": "per_variable", "values": {}},
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "Kn",
                                "range": {"start": 0.001, "stop": 1000.0, "count": 61, "scale": "log"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "fFS_vs_Kn_plot",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Fuchs-Sutugin correction factor f_FS as a function of Knudsen number Kn (log-log scale). Flat at 1 for Kn ≪ 1, then falls through the transition regime, asymptoting to ∝ 1/Kn for Kn ≫ 1.",
                            "x": {"variable": "Kn", "label": "Knudsen number Kn (dimensionless)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "f_FS", "label": "Correction factor f_FS (dimensionless)"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "fFS_vs_alpha",
                    "description": "Sweep accommodation coefficient α from 0.01 to 1.0 log-spaced at Kn=1.0 (middle of transition regime). f_FS increases with α: at α=1 f_FS ≈ 0.4946; as α → 0, both the numerator and denominator shrink but the denominator is less sensitive, so f_FS → 0. Illustrates how poor accommodation (low α) suppresses mass transfer in addition to the geometric Knudsen-number effect.",
                    "initial_state": {"type": "per_variable", "values": {}},
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "α",
                                "range": {"start": 0.01, "stop": 1.0, "count": 51, "scale": "log"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "fFS_vs_alpha_plot",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Fuchs-Sutugin correction factor f_FS as a function of accommodation coefficient α at Kn=1.0. f_FS increases monotonically from near-zero (poor accommodation) to ≈0.4946 (perfect accommodation).",
                            "x": {"variable": "α", "label": "Accommodation coefficient α"},
                            "y": {"variable": "f_FS", "label": "Correction factor f_FS (dimensionless)"}
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
